.TH "sg_alloc_table_chained" 9 "sg_alloc_table_chained" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sg_alloc_table_chained \- Allocate and chain SGLs in an sg table
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" sg_alloc_table_chained
.BI "(struct sg_table *table "  ","
.BI "int nents "  ","
.BI "struct scatterlist *first_chunk "  ","
.BI "unsigned nents_first_chunk "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "table" 12
The sg table header to use
.IP "nents" 12
Number of entries in sg list
.IP "first_chunk" 12
first SGL
.IP "nents_first_chunk" 12
number of the SGL of \fIfirst_chunk\fP
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Allocate and chain SGLs in an sg table. If \fInents\fP\fI\fP is larger than
\fInents_first_chunk\fP a chained sg table will be setup. \fIfirst_chunk\fP is
ignored if nents_first_chunk <= 1 because user expects the SGL points
non-chain SGL.
